NAME
    update - modify a single record

SYNOPSIS
    update <model> <id> [field=value ...]
    update <model> <id> '<json>'
    echo '<json>' | update <model> <id>
    update . [field=value ...]

DESCRIPTION
    Updates a single existing record. Specify the model and record ID,
    or use "." when in a record directory (/api/data/<model>/<id>).

    Fields can be updated by specifying field=value pairs on the
    command line, or by piping a JSON object to stdin.

    For bulk updates, use update_bulk instead.

OPTIONS
    field=value
        Set a field value. Can be repeated for multiple fields.
        Only specified fields are updated; others remain unchanged.

EXAMPLES
    update users abc-123 status=active
        Update a specific field

    update users abc-123 status=active name="John Doe"
        Update multiple fields

    update users abc-123 '{"status":"active","role":"admin"}'
        Update with inline JSON

    echo '{"status":"active"}' | update users abc-123
        Update from JSON via stdin

    update . status=active
        Update current record (when in /api/data/users/abc-123)

EXIT STATUS
    0   Success
    1   Error (record not found, validation failed, etc.)

SEE ALSO
    update_bulk, insert, delete, select, describe
